Package: shinymvu
Title: The Elm Architecture for Shiny Applications
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: 
    person("shinymvu authors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "shinymvu@example.com")
Description: Implements the Model-View-Update (MVU) pattern, also known as
    The Elm Architecture (TEA), for Shiny applications using Alpine.js as
    the client-side rendering engine. Provides a reactive runtime loop
    where the user defines three pure functions (init, update, view) and
    the package handles all WebSocket plumbing. Includes enum-based message
    types with exhaustive pattern matching, declarative input helpers, Shiny
    module support, and testing utilities for pure update functions.
